HEADWORD: Dephlegmation
<hw>De`phleg*ma"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧flegmation</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>The
operation of separating water from spirits and acids, by evaporation or
repeated distillation; -- called also <altname>concentration</altname>,
especially when acids are the subject of it.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dephlegmator</ent>⟦br⟧
